 able to list their tickets and create a new ticket through POST. If comments endpoint exists, allow frontend-only or backend comment based on API availability. No email sending, no file attachments. Preserve Phase 4 premium support UI. Add loading, empty, error, success, retry, and validation states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"156-phase5-frontend-client-analytics-governance-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Client Analytics and Governance to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/analytics and /portal/governance\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /portal/analytics to /api/v1/analytics/client and /portal/governance to /api/v1/governance. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static data with backend summaries and governance records. Governance read actions may be backend-connected if endpoint exists, otherwise keep read-only. Preserve Phase 4 visual design, charts, filters, and mobile behavior. Add loading, empty, error, and retry states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"158-phase5-frontend-admin-dashboard-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Dashboard to backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/dashboard\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin and /admin/dashboard to backend /api/v1/dashboard/admin. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace static admin dashboard data with backend data. Preserve Phase 4 premium admin UI. Add loading, empty, error, retry states. Admin dashboard should show clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance,  based on database records. No fake live data. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"159-phase5-frontend-admin-clients-users-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Clients and Users to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/clients and /admin/users\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/clients and /admin/users to backend CRUD APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin clients page should list, search/filter, create, edit, archive if API supports it. Admin users page should list, search/filter, create, edit role/status, deactivate if API supports it. Use modals or drawers that preserve existing UI. Add loading, empty, error, success, validation, and retry states. Enforce frontend role visibility based on backend current user, but backend remains source of truth. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"160-phase5-frontend-admin-projects-aiops-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Projects and AI Operations to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/projects and /admin/ai-operations\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/projects and /admin/ai-operations to backend CRUD APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin projects page should list, filter, create, edit, archive projects if API supports it. Admin AI operations page should list, filter, create, edit, assign owner, update status/health/governance if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 UI with drawers/modals. No live agent runtime. Add loading, empty, error, success states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"161-phase5-frontend-admin-documents-billing-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Documents and Billing to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/documents and /admin/billing\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/documents to backend document metadata CRUD and /admin/billing to invoice metadata CRUD. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Documents are metadata-only, no upload/download/storage. Billing is invoice metadata-only, no payment/PDF. Admin should list, create metadata, edit metadata, archive if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 UI and disabled future integration controls. Add loading, empty, error, success, validation states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"162-phase5-frontend-admin-support-governance-api\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect Admin Support and Governance to backend CRUD\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-frontend-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"/admin/support and /admin/governance\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect /admin/support to backend support ticket APIs and /admin/governance to backend governance APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Admin support should list, filter, assign, update status, and optionally add local/backend comment depending on API. Admin governance should list, filter, create, update status, assign reviewer if API supports it. Preserve Phase 4 premium UI. No email, no attachments, no compliance guarantees. Add loading, empty, error, success, retry states. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"165-phase5-remove-old-local-preview-data-dependency\",\n    \"title\": \"Reduce dependency on Phase 4 local mock data in portal admin\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-cleanup\",\n    \"target\": \"mock data cleanup\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Reduce reliance on Phase 4 local mock data for portal/admin pages now connected to backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Keep local mock data only as fallback or for non-backend preview sections. Portal/admin dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance,clients, and users should prefer backend API data. Do not delete shared mock data if still used safely by non-integrated components, but clearly separate backend-connected data from fallback data. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"166-phase5-dev-environment-docs\",\n    \"title\": \"Document local dev environment for MVP backend\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"local dev documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_MVP_BACKEND.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document how to install backend dependencies, create .env from .env.example, initialize SQLite, run seed, start backend, start frontend, configure NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL, login with seeded dev users, and test portal/admin flows. Document that this phase is local/dev MVP only and does not include AWS, storage, payments, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth hardening, or backend for GFF AI tools. Include troubleshooting for CORS, missing DB, invalid token, and seed rerun. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"167-phase5-security-limitations-docs\",\n    \"title\": \"Document MVP security limitations and Phase 6 hardening\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"security documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_SECURITY_LIMITATIONS.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document MVP security limitations honestly: JWT in localStorage or dev storage, SQLite local DB, local seed users, no production password reset, no MFA, no refresh token hardening, no httpOnly secure cookie implementation unless already done, no rate limiting, no audit-grade logs, no production RBAC review, no file scanning, no payment compliance. Document required Phase 6 hardening steps: production database, httpOnly secure cookies or hardened session strategy, refresh token rotation, password reset, MFA/SSO optional, rate limiting, audit logs, secrets management, deployment config, CORS hardening. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"168-phase5-backend-frontend-smoke-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Run backend and frontend smoke QA\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-quality\",\n    \"target\": \"local full stack smoke QA\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform a local full-stack smoke QA for Phase 5. Do not add features unless fixing small clear issues. Verify backend can start, health endpoint works, database initializes, seed script works, dev users can login, /auth/me returns current user, client user cannot access admin APIs, admin user can access admin APIs, client portal dashboard fetches data, admin dashboard fetches data, support ticket create works, documents are metadata-only, invoices are metadata-only. Verify frontend builds. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Run available backend checks/tests and frontend lint/build. Fix only issues found during smoke QA.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"169-phase5-no-gff-tools-backend-regression-audit\",\n    \"title\": \"Audit that GFF AI tools remain frontend-only\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-safety\",\n    \"target\": \"GFF AI tools backend exclusion\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Audit that Phase 3 GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and were not accidentally connected to backend. Do not touch landing page. Check /build/blueprint, /build/roi, /build/proposal, /build/assessment, /build/sandbox, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio, /build/talk. These should not call the new backend APIs in Phase 5. They may still use local state, localStorage, deterministic calculations, and frontend preview behavior. If accidental backend integration exists in these tools, remove it and restore frontend-only behavior. Do not change their UI unless required to remove backend calls. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"170-phase5-final-mvp-backend-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Final Phase 5 MVP backend QA\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase5-final-qa\",\n    \"target\": \"MVP backend auth RBAC portal admin integration\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for Phase 5. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify local/dev backend exists and runs. Verify SQLite database setup. Verify seed data and dev users. Verify JWT login, auth/me, logout, RBAC, client data scoping, admin access. Verify CRUD APIs for clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, invoices metadata, support tickets, governance, dashboard summaries, analytics summaries. Verify frontend login connects to backend. Verify client portal pages use backend data: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Verify admin pages use backend data: Dashboard, Clients, Users, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings. Verify no AWS, storage, payment, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth, or backend for GFF AI tools was added. Verify landing page unchanged. Run backend tests/checks if available, backend startup/import checks, npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, local dev login credentials from seed docs, and TODOs for Phase 6 production hardening.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"171-phase6-aws-preflight-final-scope-audit\",\n    \"title\": \"Phase 6 AWS final scope audit\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-audit\",\n    \"target\": \"final AWS DynamoDB S3 product completion\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Audit the current Phase 5 implementation before AWS conversion. Do not edit files. Confirm that login, admin, client portal, local backend, SQLite models, JWT auth, RBAC, CRUD APIs, frontend API client, and portal/admin pages exist. Confirm GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and must not receive backend integration. Produce a short final implementation checklist only. Phase 6 must only move the MVP product from local SQLite to AWS DynamoDB and S3, connect document uploads/downloads, update env configuration, seed AWS data, and run final QA. Do not add new product features. Do not add payment, OTP, email, SSO, rate limiting, advanced security, audit logs, or backend for Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, Foundry Studio, or Talk to Agent.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"172-phase6-aws-env-and-config\",\n    \"title\": \"Add AWS env config\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-config\",\n    \"target\": \"backend AWS environment configuration\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add final AWS configuration to the backend. Do not touch landing page. Do not modify GFF AI tools. Update backend env example and settings/config to support AWS_REGION, AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE, DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE, DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE, DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TYPE_INDEX, S3_DOCUMENTS_BUCKET, S3_DOCUMENTS_PREFIX, JWT_SECRET, ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES, CORS_ORIGINS, and FRONTEND_BASE_URL. Keep local development support if it already exists. Do not commit real secrets. Do not add unnecessary security features. Run backend import check.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"173-phase6-dynamodb-table-documentation\",\n    \"title\": \"Document final DynamoDB tables\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"DynamoDB table setup documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md with the exact AWS resources required. Document only three DynamoDB tables: GFF_USERS with primary key email, GFF_CLIENTS with primary key client_id, and GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS with PK and SK plus GSI1 using GSI1PK and GSI1SK. Document that GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS stores Projects, AI Operations, Documents metadata, Invoices metadata, Support Tickets, and Governance Items. Document one S3 bucket for portal documents. Include required backend and frontend env keys. Keep documentation concise.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"174-phase6-dynamodb-client-and-repositories\",\n    \"title\": \"Create DynamoDB client and repository layer\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-backend\",\n    \"target\": \"DynamoDB repository layer\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create a simple DynamoDB client and repository layer for the backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace direct SQLite usage in portal/admin APIs with DynamoDB repository functions. Create repositories for users, clients, and portal items. Portal items must support entity types: PROJECT, AI_OPERATION, DOCUMENT, INVOICE, SUPPORT, GOVERNANCE. Keep implementation simple and readable. Use boto3 if backend is Python/FastAPI. Do not add unnecessary abstraction. Run backend import check.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb\",\n    \"title\": \"Move auth users to DynamoDB\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-auth\",\n    \"target\": \"DynamoDB-backed login\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Update auth to read users from the GFF_USERS DynamoDB table. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Login must verify email and password_hash from DynamoDB. /auth/me must return current user from DynamoDB. Keep JWT behavior from Phase 5. Roles are only gff_admin, client_admin, client_member. Do not add forgot password, OTP, SSO, refresh token, or production cookie flow. Run backend check.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"176-phase6-clients-and-portal-items-dynamodb\",\n    \"title\": \"Move clients and portal CRUD to DynamoDB\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-backend\",\n    \"target\": \"DynamoDB-backed portal admin CRUD\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Update CRUD APIs for clients, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, invoices metadata, support tickets, and governance items to use DynamoDB. Use GFF_CLIENTS for clients and GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS for all other portal/admin items. Admin users can access all records. Client users can access only their own client_id records. Keep endpoints from Phase 5. Do not add new routes unless required to keep current frontend working. Run backend check.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"177-phase6-dashboard-analytics-dynamodb\",\n    \"title\": \"Use DynamoDB for dashboard and analytics summaries\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-backend\",\n    \"target\": \"dashboard analytics DynamoDB\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Update dashboard and analytics summary endpoints to compute from DynamoDB records. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Client dashboard must count only that user's client_id records. Admin dashboard must summarize all clients and all portal items. Analytics should stay simple: counts by status, phase, support priority, invoice status, AI operation health, and governance severity. Do not add new analytics features. Run backend check.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"178-phase6-s3-document-files\",\n    \"title\": \"Add S3 document upload and download\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-s3\",\n    \"target\": \"portal document file storage\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add S3 support only for portal/admin documents. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Backend should upload document files to S3 under clients/<client_id>/documents/<document_id>/<filename>. Store metadata in GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS as DOCUMENT records. Add backend endpoints for document upload and download or signed download URL if simpler. Keep it minimal. Do not add virus scanning, advanced permissions, OCR, previews, or versioning. Ensure client users can only access documents for their client_id. Run backend check.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"179-phase6-frontend-documents-s3-integration\",\n    \"title\": \"Connect frontend document upload and download\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-frontend\",\n    \"target\": \"documents UI S3 integration\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Connect client and admin document pages to the S3-backed document endpoints. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Client portal documents should list documents, upload document if allowed, and download/view document link. Admin documents should list, create metadata/upload file, edit metadata, and download/view document link. Keep UI simple. Do not add previews, OCR, version history, or advanced file management. Add loading, error, and success states. Run frontend lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"180-phase6-seed-aws-data\",\n    \"title\": \"Create AWS DynamoDB seed script\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-data\",\n    \"target\": \"AWS seed data\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update seed script to seed DynamoDB tables with final MVP data. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Seed users for gff_admin, client_admin, and client_member only. Seed 2 representative clients, projects, AI operations, document metadata, invoices, support tickets, and governance items. Do not seed fake real client names or logos. Document seed credentials in Phase 6 docs. Ensure seed can be safely rerun without duplicate records. Run seed only if environment is configured.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"181-phase6-frontend-env-and-api-finalization\",\n    \"title\": \"Finalize frontend API environment integration\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-frontend\",\n    \"target\": \"frontend production env\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Finalize frontend environment usage. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Ensure portal/admin frontend uses NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL for backend calls. Ensure NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_UPLOADS_ENABLED controls document upload visibility if implemented. Remove local preview dependency from portal/admin pages except safe fallback states. Do not connect GFF AI tools to backend. Run frontend lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"182-phase6-cors-and-deployment-config\",\n    \"title\": \"Finalize CORS and deployment config\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-deployment\",\n    \"target\": \"backend frontend deployment readiness\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Finalize minimal deployment configuration. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Backend must read CORS_ORIGINS from env and allow the frontend domain. Update docs with backend start command, frontend build command, required env variables, and AWS resource names. Do not add Docker or cloud hosting files unless already required by the current deployment approach. Keep this simple and MVP-ready. Run backend check and frontend build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"183-phase6-final-product-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Final product QA\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-final-qa\",\n    \"target\": \"full working MVP product\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for the full MVP product. Do not add new features. Verify login works with DynamoDB users. Verify RBAC works for gff_admin, client_admin, and client_member. Verify admin can manage clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, and governance items. Verify client portal can view its own dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, and governance. Verify support ticket creation works. Verify document upload/download works through S3. Verify dashboard and analytics use DynamoDB data. Verify invoices are metadata only and no payment exists. Verify GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and hardcoded. Verify no AWS backend is added for Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, Foundry Studio, or Talk to Agent. Verify landing page unchanged. Run backend checks and frontend lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"184-phase6-final-wrap-up-docs\",\n    \"title\": \"Final wrap-up documentation\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase6-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"final product handoff docs\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create final concise handoff documentation. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Update docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md with AWS tables, S3 bucket, env keys, seed users, local run commands, production run commands, frontend env, backend env, and final scope. Clearly state that GFF AI tools are frontend-only dummy/hardcoded and not backend-connected. Keep the document short and practical. Run build only if docs affect build.\"\n  }\n]\n","success":true}],"durationMs":20}}
