ed SHA-256 hash), and error (showing specific messages). I'm also now analyzing `app/portal/documents/page.tsx` for integration.\n\n\n**Refining Project Scope**\n\nI'm now diving into the implementation details of the upload form's state management. I'm focusing on the component's state variables: `uploadTitle`, `uploadCategory`, `uploadProjectId`, `uploadVersion`, `uploadVisibility`, `uploadDescription`, `uploading`, `uploadError`, `uploadSuccess`, and `uploadedDocInfo`. I'm starting to think through the interaction between the form fields and the API calls. I'm also now analyzing the best way to handle the available projects, fetched with the `useEffect` hook, from `/api/v1/projects`, ensuring they're scoped correctly to the user's `client_id`. I'm leaning toward getting that client id from `/api/v1/auth/me`.\n\n\n**Analyzing Project Fetching**\n\nI'm now closely examining the `useEffect` hook's project fetching. The code robustly handles different backend responses. It correctly manages token retrieval from `localStorage` and gracefully handles potential errors. I'm focusing on how the backend data is processed and checking that the array response for projects is parsed correctly.\n\n\n\n**Defining Upload Details**\n\nI'm now integrating the form data to prepare for the API call. I'm focusing on crafting the request body, including the file itself, and constructing the `formData` with `client_id` (derived from `/api/v1/auth/me`), `project_id`, `title`, and other details. I'm ensuring all the necessary fields are included before proceeding with the file upload.\n\n\n**Finalizing Upload Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the API call itself. I've constructed the `formData` object, carefully including all necessary details such as the title, description, and client-derived information. I'm currently testing the upload and error handling, making sure it gracefully displays success and failure messages to the user. I'm also ensuring the toast notifications are correctly triggered and displaying useful information.\n\n\n**Evaluating Download Implementation**\n\nI'm now investigating the download functionality, specifically in relation to the document list refresh and integration with the existing download button in the document drawer. The plan is to explore `app/portal/documents/page.tsx` more closely, specifically around the simulated download functionality, to improve it.\n\n\n"}}
