{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:05:50.665Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"buqi72fr","input":{"summary":"### Summary of Investigation & Resolution\n\n#### 1. Context & Objectives\nThe task was to implement **S3 document upload and download** for both the client portal and admin registry. The backend had already added the endpoint `/api/v1/documents/upload` and `/api/v1/documents/download/{id}`, along with an S3 local storage manager and a security smoke test in `test_backend_smoke.py`. However, the frontend pages (`/portal/documents`, `/portal/documents/[id]`, `/admin/documents`, `/portal/governance`) were still using mock/simulated states and contained a structural payload mismatch where they expected wrapped lists instead of the raw JSON arrays returned by the backend.\n\n#### 2. Actions & Implementation Details\n- **Dynamic API Compatibility (Array parsing)**: Fixed a structural payload mismatch by updating the fetching mechanisms in `ClientDocumentsPage`, `AdminDocumentsPage`, and `ClientGovernancePage` to robustly check if the returned payload is a raw array `[...]` (returned by the mock DynamoDB API) or an object containing `{success: true, documents: [...]}`.\n- **Real S3 Downloads**: Updated the download triggers on the `/portal/documents` card view, `/portal/documents` list view, `/portal/documents/[id]` detail view, and `/admin/documents` registry view to perform real binary fetches with authentication headers from `/api/v1/documents/download/{id}`. This triggers an automated browser blob download seamlessly.\n- **Premium Secure Multipart Ingestion Modal**:\n  - Replaced the mock click handlers in `/portal/documents` with a modern, premium **Secure Document Ingestion Modal**.\n  - Enabled clients to choose local files, specify titles, category classifications (SOW, Proposals, Architecture, Reports, etc.), versioning, and link files to their active sandboxed projects.\n  - Resolved client-scoping parameters by fetching current session details from `/api/v1/auth/me` and linking uploads automatically to the client's respective database ID.\n- **Admin Multi-Part S3 Uploads**:\n  - Replaced the old non-existent `POST /api/v1/documents` endpoint on the admin deck with the correct secure multipart `POST /api/v1/documents/upload` endpoint.\n  - Implemented client account resolution logic on the admin side by matching chosen preview clients against the live client list from `/api/v1/clients` to dynamically fetch the correct numeric client ID.\n  - Integrated a premium file-select asset input inside the admin registry drawer.\n\n#### 3. Validation & Quality Checks\n- Ran **ESLint** across the frontend and confirmed **zero syntax, import, or linting errors**.\n- Executed **Pytest** on `backend/app/test_backend_smoke.py` and confirmed all 8 core backend and security dependency checks passed with **100% success**.\n- Checked layout responsiveness, accessibility cues (accessible labels, disabled states during upload, semantic input elements, micro-interactions), and strict alignment with the premium 2026 GFF AI visual guidelines.","verified":true}}}
